Summary: Remove storage data for October for an OSaaS instance
Creator: Bonev, Georgi
Description: Hello Team, We have a stakeholder which enabled continuous backup for their Object Store instances, but as this is tied to a significant cost, they decided to that they will disable the feature. All backup and point in time data for their instances was removed for their accounts. Creator: Hasan, Waseem
Description: *Summary:* During recent testing on the integration landscape, we identified a significant number of metered order events. These events are being generated due to multiple calls made by the oms-metering service to the unified metering service. We noticed that calls with identical IDs are not being deduplicated, contrary to our expectations based on the provided documentation. Screenshots attached below illustrate the excessive number of metered order events observed during the testing phase. According to the documentation provided in [https://pages.github.tools.sap/metering/documentation/docs/unified-metering/meter-your-app/#usage-schema-for-sap-btp] ||Field||Description||Type||Required||Supported Values||Constraints|| |id|A unique identifier for usage entry.|string|Optional|For example: â€œc2214e4e-9629-42a0-8fbb-5d204c29c21dâ€|The value is always a GUID. This field is used to avoid retransmission duplications.| However, the current behavior indicates that the unified metering service is not ignoring multiple calls with the same ID, leading to duplicated entries. This inconsistency with our understanding of the documentation necessitates further investigation. * We seek clarification on our interpretation of the documentation regarding idempotency and deduplication processes within the unified metering service. * Recommendations for any adjustments in configurations or additional measures to ensure that idempotency is maintained would be highly appreciated.
Business Impact: potentially metering the same order or transaction multiple times
Steps to Duplicate: Send the same metering call with the same id to the integration metering instance with Id *c4-distributed-order-management-integration* is metering multiple times for the same event.
